<h1>Aquaint Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>Aquaint is a fast and easy way to share your social media profiles. You can follow a friend you've just met and have access to all their social media accounts all on one profile. Because of these services you as the user will need to share some information with us and we know this will affect your privacy. The information we collect will be purely based on your say so.</p>

<p>Protection of your private information is our priority. This Statement of Privacy applies to Aquaint and governs data collection and usage. For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, unless otherwise noted, all references to Aquaint include www.aquaint.io and Aquaint. The Aquaint website gives information on the iOS application. By using the iOS application Aquaint, you consent to the data practices described in this statement.</p>

<h3>Information Collected</h3>
<p>Aquaint may collect personally identifiable information such as your social media username or user id. We may gather additional personal or non-personal information in the future.</p>

<p>Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable information or personally sensitive data through Aquaint's public message  boards, this information may be collected and used by others.</p>

<p>Aquaint encourages you to review the privacy statements of websites you choose to link to from Aquaint so that you can understand how those websites collect, use and share your information. Aquaint is not responsible for the privacy statements or other content on websites or services outside of the Aquaint application.</p>

<h3>Use of Personal Information</h3>
<p>Aquaint collects and uses your personal information to operate and deliver services you have requested. Personal information such as email addresses and phone numbers will not be publicly displayed. Aquaint encrypts and stores passwords securely.</p>

<p>Aquaint does not sell, rent or lease its customer list to third parties.</p>

<p>Aquaint will disclose your personal information, without notice. Only if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to: (a) conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on Aquaint; (b) protect and defend the rights or property of Aquaint; and, (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect the personal safety of Aquaint, or the public.</p>

<h3>Security of your Personal Information</h3>

<p>Aquaint secures your personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure.</p>

<h3>Changes to this Statement</h3>
<p>Aquaint will occasionally update this Statement of Privacy to reflect company and customer feedback. Aquaint encourages you to periodically review this Statement to be informed of how Aquaint is protecting your information.</p>

<h3>Contact Information</h3>
<p>Aquaint welcomes your questions or comments regarding this Statement of Privacy. If you believe that Aquaint has now adhered to this Statement, please contact Aquaint at:</p>

<p>Email Address: <b><a href="mailto:support@aquaint.us?Subject=Privacy%20Policy%20Question">support@aquaint.us</a></b></p>

<p>Effective as of September 20, 2016</p>
